<TEXT>
the tarttongued immigration chief 
suggested a congressman stick his finger in an electrical socket 
after he alleged her department was riddled with corruption 
you as a person you do not deserve to be called by a name 
other than fumble face shrieked immigration commissioner miriam 
defensor santiago in a statement to a manila television station on 
tuesday 
and you can go stick your finger in the wall socket 
mrs santiago a former judge made the remark in response to 
rep mario joaquins claim in the house of reprsentatives on monday 
that the commission on immigration and deportation was fraught with 
corruption 
mrs santiago said she wanted to challenge joaquin to a fist 
fight to defend her reputation there was no immediate response 
from the congressman 
since her appointment last year mrs santiago has cultivated a 
reputation for honesty and efficiency in a bureaucracy riddled with 
graft corruption and inefficiency 
she once warned immigration officers at manila airport that she 
was aware of their corrupt practices and would cut them into small 
pieces and feed you to the sharks in manila bay 
she then added that the sharks would probably not devour the 
officials out of professional courtesy 
critics however claim the commission is still corrupt and that 
mrs santiago has run roughshod over employees to enhance her 
reputation and launch a political career 
