william niskanean a former economic adviser to president reagan 
according to riegles plan the government would buy back many of 
the notes and loans it sold at discounts to the new owners of the 
institutions it merged in 1988 before sept 30 
the plan also would include in the 1989 budget the cost of 
closing and paying off depositors in the worst of the 350 insolvent 
but stilloperating sampls 
the federal deposit insurance corp has taken control of over 120 
of those institutions in the two months since bush announced his sampl 
proposal and plans to take control of another 100 before the end of 
march 
however without the needed money in the government insurance 
funds to pay off their depositors or subsidize their mergers those 
sampls are still operating with losses mounting in the tens of 
millions of dollars daily 
the gao estimated the cost of the 1988 sampl closings and mergers 
at 37 billion assuming all could be paid for immediately rather 
than financed and not including the 6 billion to 8 billion in tax 
breaks that were a part of some packages 
both administration and congressional experts put the 
presentvalue cost of resolving the other 350 insolvent institutions 
