pakhtusov a military attache at the soviet embassy in 
washington was ordered home after the fbi said it caught him 
receiving sensitive information 
a us source alleged the 35yearold soviet was a member of gru 
the soviet militarys intelligence arm 
over the years when one superpower expelled a diplomat on spying 
charges the other nation has responded in kind 
in october 1986 after 25 soviet diplomats were ordered out of 
the soviet un mission in new york the kremlin expelled five 
american diplomats 
