<TEXT>
animals weary of wading through deep 
crusty snow have taken to highways and railroad tracks and more 
than 600 moose and 94 caribou have been killed this winter 
officials said 
the animals have been killed by trains or motor vehicles in 
anchorage the interior and on the kenai peninsula officials for 
state agencies say 
theres a tendency for them to walk on the trails and the 
biggest trails available to them are the tracks and the roads 
said carl grauvogel a state wildlife biologist in palmer 
salting could be a big factor 
ive seen moose kneeling right in the highways said mike 
roscovius fish and wildlife protection division officer in 
glennallen they must be licking the pavement for salt because 
thats all that would be there 
