bush praised derwinski as uniquely qualified to lead the new 
agency because he has the skill of a seasoned legislator the 
patience of a practical administrator the finesse of a diplomat and 
the heart of a man who knows what it means to start his government 
career as a private in the united states army 
derwinski is a former 12term member of the house from illinois 
who served in highlevel state department posts in the reagan 
administration he served in the army in 19451946 and took part in 
the occupation of japan 
the veterans department formed from the old veterans 
administration is the secondlargest agency of the government 
behind the defense department with 240000 employees its annual 
spending of about 29 billion is the fifth largest among agencies 
it expects to keep the short title from its past va 
veterans organizations for years sought the greater clout they 
thought cabinet rank would give them but it took an electionyear 
conversion by former president reagan last year to put the idea 
across 
derwinski has six months to make organizational changes he 
believes necessary but already hes decided they wont be 
drastic 
in an interview earlier this week he repeated a warning he has 
been giving veterans groups along with promises to drop in for a 
beer at their local halls that in the next four years there are 
