debate aging derwinski said the patients needs start to 
change it ultimately means longterm health care rather than 
dramatic surgical procedures 
there are more than 27 million veterans counting dependents a 
third of the nation is eligible for one or another of the services 
provided by the huge but fairly uncomplicated bureaucracy 
dispensing medical care and 17 billion a year in pensions and other 
money benefits and operating 111 national ceremonies 
with 172 hospitals 229 outpatient clinics and scores of other 
installations the agency runs the largest medical care system in 
the country caring for 14 million hospital patients annually 
the vas motto comes from lincolns second inaugural address 
to care for him who shall have borne the battle and for his widow 
and his orphan the agency traces its history to the plymouth 
colony law of 1636 for the maintenance of members disabled in the 
pequot indian war though the va was formed only in 1930 to 
consolidate veterans program in other departments 
