into san francisco and began rounding up the villagers the soldiers 
reportedly found rebel arms and mines in at least one house 
the day after the killings the villagers told the associated 
press that about 45 of them had been herded into the small 
schoolhouse the troopers working from a list separated the 10 
victims and marched them away 
guandique citing testimony from galvez and the soldiers said 
beltran ordered the captured mines to be placed along a path and 
detonated as the detainees were marched past but the devices did 
not explode on the first try 
several soldiers surrounded the prisoners and held them in place 
while another trooper fetched a new battery to detonate the mines 
guandique said 
the mines were finally detonated killing or wounding all the 
prisoners who were then riddled with rifle fire and dispatched with 
a shot to the head guandique said 
guandique quoted galvez and others as saying beltran also ordered 
the schoolhouse to be mined and blown up but he was either 
dissuaded or desisted when subordinates balked 
it could have been 50 people instead of 10 guandique said 
