<TEXT>
the controversy over a 1985 crash in newfoundland 
that killed 256 americans was revived wednesday with the leaking of 
a transport department report questioning the conclusions of the 
official investigation 
the canadian aviation safety board concluded after a threeyear 
investigation that ice on the planes wings probably caused it to 
crash 
but the ottawa citizen reported wednesday that an internal report 
by the transport department or transport canada rejected the 
safety boards majority conclusion and said the investigation was 
mismanaged 
the transport canada review does not substantiate the 
conclusion that the aircraft stalled probably due to 
icecontaminated wings the citizen quoted the report as saying 
it is the opinion of the aviation safety programs branch that the 
cause of this accident is considered to be undetermined 
transportation minister benoit bouchard announced last week he 
had accepted the boards conclusion he ruled out a judicial inquiry 
into the boards handling of the investigation 
sandra wood spokesman for transport canada said bouchard made 
his statement last week based on recommendations from aides and did 
not know about the critical study 
claude lafrance an assistant deputy transport minister told a 
